# Climate Change Laws of the World (CCLW)

**Theme:** Governance & Climate Law / Climate Policy
**Source:** Grantham Research Institute on Climate Change and the Environment, LSE (in partnership with Climate Policy Radar and Sabin Center, Columbia Law School)
**Geographic Coverage:** Global (196 UNFCCC parties + EU + non-UN territories including Taiwan, Palestine, Western Sahara; 200+ jurisdictions total)
**Time Coverage:** ~1947–present (continuously updated; methodology last updated August 2024)
**Unit of Observation:** Law, policy, or UNFCCC submission (national level)
**Format:** Web (interactive search), downloadable CSV
**Access:** [climate-laws.org](https://climate-laws.org/) |
[Download whole database (CSV)](https://climate-laws.org/search)
**License:** Free to access; see [Terms of Use](https://climate-laws.org/terms-of-use)
**Last Verified:** April 2026

